article.headline: High Point 70, Savannah St. 49
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 15 points, and High Point took an early lead and never trailed again in a 70-49 victory over Savannah State on Tuesday night. Landon Quick had 12 points and seven rebounds, and Jerrald Minnis scored 11 for High Point (17-8). Javon Randolph led Savannah State with 14 points. Savannah State (10-16) had its only lead when Patrick Hardy hit a 3-pointer 48 seconds into the game to put the Tigers ahead 3-2. High Point responded with a trey by Troy Bowen, who finished with nine points, a little more than a minute later to make it 5-3 and stretched the lead to as many as 17 points, 33-16, with four minutes left in the first half. High Point led 35-21 at halftime and used a 10-2 run capped by a Quick layup late in the second half to expand the Savannah State deficit to 26 points, 66-40, with 1:49 left.
